"Electronic Ticket" Unique to Recipient Items Setouchi City added by Furusato Taxpay: Sanyo Newspaper Digital | San Diego
"E Street Gift."
i'll contact the dedicated equipment and settle it.
Setouchi City announced on July 27 that it would add its own electronic ticket "e-machi Gift" to the home tax return goods.
It can be used by member stores in the city from November.
It was the first municipality in the prefecture.
If you pay home tax and choose an electronic ticket as a return item, 30% of the donation will be sent to the designated smartphone.
At the time of purchase, the shop shows the screen of the ticket, and the store contacts the stamped equipment and settles it.
It cannot be sold or sold.
It usually takes a certain amount of time from application to arrival, but it is possible to receive an electronic ticket instantly.
Tourists can use it easily.
In addition to the five hometown tax portals, it is also available on two special sites in the city.
The current membership is 13 stores, and by the end of this fiscal year it aims to reach 100 stores.
In June, the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications established a new system to regulate local products in order to prevent excessive competition among municipalities, with the amount of return goods raised to less than 30% of donations.
The city says, "It is planned to be a member of a local product company and within the guidelines."
In the 18th year of Setouchi City, the amount of hometown tax is about 430 million yen.
