Driving at high heels is dangerous!
Accidents involving the wrong pedal of young people - Yahoo! News
Violations against road traffic laws
The number of reports on accidents caused by malfunctions such as pedal mistakes is increasing, but it is a big mistake to think that this is a problem only for elderly drivers.
According to the 2015 National Police Agency data, there were more than 1080 cases in the age of 24 years and 1032 cases over 75 years.
It is important to call attention to young people as well.
are you going to take your feet?
is it safe?
There is no description of the gender ratio or cause of this data, but unlike the elderly who are often thought to be due to the decline of the body, such as driving skills and reflexes, in the younger generation, it is possible to make mistakes due to accidental mistakes due to music and conversation etc.
In particular, women choose a variety of shoes depending on the day's clothes, such as high heels, pamps, sandals and mulles, and drive as they are.
Although some people know that it is not suitable for driving, it is troublesome to change clothes, some people do not think that it may lead to danger at all, and many people drive without hesitation.
However, driving in high heels and sandals violates road traffic laws.
One is to ensure that the steering wheel, brakes and other operations are operated. Article 70 of the Act stipulates that the operation should not be carried out to cause accidents and harm to people.
The other is Article 71, which stipulates that the driver must comply with the matters stipulated by the Public Safety Commission of each prefecture.For example, in Article 12 of the Enforcement Regulations of the Miyazaki Prefectural Road Traffic Law, there is a statement that the driver must not drive a vehicle (except light vehicles) by wearing shoes in a manner that prevents driving operations, such as "slippers, suspensions, high heels, etc."
It is similar to the intention of each prefecture to consider driving as a violation of "a footwear that can prevent operation" even if it is not specified as a high heel.
So why is driving at high heels dangerous?
It is obvious considering the basics of safely pedaling.
For safe and secure pedal operation, first place the foot strap on the floor, place the foot perpendicular to the brake pedal, and when stepping on the accelerator pedal, tilt the foot tip to the right as the starting point.
At this time, regardless of the behavior of the car, it is important to keep the lid firmly fixed so that it does not break.
However, in high heels, the area where the kato is grounded on the floor is small, and it always blurs out, and because the height of the heel has an angle on the entire foot, the area of the foot that is grounded on the pedal is smaller and it is difficult to make fine adjustments.
This may lead to danger.
In addition, most cars have floor carpets, but this material is easy to pull a high heel, and sometimes when it comes to a sudden brake, the heel is pulled and the pedal cannot be stepped, or the heel is removed in the time signature that the heel is pulled, and it can not be stepped inside the pedal.
In addition, there are cases where the heel is pulled to the back side of the pedal when stepping back from the pedal, and the accelerator pedal is no longer returned.
Toyota and Subaru to Accelerate Joint Development (Response) - Yahoo!News
Toyota and Subaru agreed to a new business capital alliance on September 27.
Toyota will acquire Subaru shares and become an affiliate of the equity method.
Since the agreement in 2005, the two companies have been working together to produce Toyota vehicles commissioned by Subaru, to supply vehicles from Toyota to Subaru, and to jointly develop the FR sports car 86.
In June of this year, we agreed to develop EV-only platforms and EV vehicles using Subaru's All-wheel drive technology and Toyota's electrification technology.
In this agreement, Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares.
Currently, Toyota's shares in Subaru are 16.83% of voting rights, but they are acquired until they reach 20%.
Subaru is an affiliate of Toyota's equity method.
On the other hand, Subaru will acquire Toyota shares equivalent to the same amount (up to 8 billion yen) as the amount required to acquire Subaru shares.
Both companies develop and strengthen cooperative relationships through business capital alliances.
Joint development of the AWD and 86/BRZ models, expansion of the THS (Toyota Hybrid System) to Subaru vehicles, coordination in the connected area, technical cooperation in the autonomous driving field, etc.
U.S., at least 3 consecutive years, 18,000 people | Shizuoka Shimbun
The U.S. Department of State announced on October 26, 2020 that it would reduce the number of refugees accepted from around the world to 18,000.
The minimum number of refugees since 1980 has been renewed for three consecutive years.
The Trump administration aims to appeal to the conservatives the strict immigration and refugee policies in the presidential election next year.
People who are expelled from the country in various places are constantly being criticized by human rights organizations.
The previous Obama administration set the limit to 110,000 in FY17, but the Trump administration, which was launched in January 2017, overturned this and reduced it to 50,000.
It has been reduced to 45,000 in fiscal 2006, and 30,000 in fiscal 2007.
