South Korea-Bulgarian Summit Meeting | Yahoo! News
According to Yonhap News, (SEOUL=Yonhap News) South Korea's President Moon Jae-in met with Bulgaria's Prime Minister Borisov during his official visit to Korea and discussed ways to expand bilateral cooperation.
This is the first visit to Korea by the Prime Minister of Bulgaria.
President Moon welcomed the visit to Korea prior to the 30th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations next year, and appreciated Prime Minister Borisov's leadership leading the development of Bulgaria.
The two leaders appreciated the continued increase in trade and investment between the two countries amid the growing global protection and tradeism, and agreed to work together to expand economic cooperation in the future.
President Moon welcomed Bulgaria's commitment to granting Korean companies the status of "strategic investors," and said he hoped that the investment of Korean companies in Bulgaria would be promoted based on this.
He stressed that while Bulgaria was promoting the introduction of nuclear power and modernization of its defense, Korea would become the best partner for Bulgaria, and called for attention and cooperation so that Korean companies could participate in the order of the Bulgarian government's nuclear power plants and the promotion of the defense industry.
The two leaders also agreed to strengthen future-oriented cooperation in the areas of battery and auto parts for electric vehicles and renewable energy.
Prime Minister Borisov hoped that close cooperation will be carried out in the ICT (Information and Communication Technology) and science and technology and education sectors led by Korea.
The peace process on the Korean Peninsula was discussed, and President Moon expressed his gratitude for the support of the Korean government's efforts to establish peace on the Korean Peninsula, including the announcement of a statement that Bulgaria would support the North-South and North-South Summit.
Prime Minister Borisov appreciated President Moon's will to build a peace regime on the Korean Peninsula and the efforts of the Korean government, and reiterated the firm support of the Bulgarian government.
The meeting was attended by Secretary of the Ministry of Trade, Industry and Energy Shigeyoshi (Son Yunmo), Chief Secretary of the Economic Affairs of Chong (President's Office), and Second Director of the State Security Office of Kim Hyun-jong.
On behalf of the Secretary of Foreign Affairs of Kang-yeong-wa during his visit to the United States, he also attended the First Secretary of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Zhao Yeong.
The local industry in Hyogo and Awaji Island, Kinki Ceramics, manufactured by Awaji Kawara, filed for quasi-self-insolvency debt of approximately ¥2 billion (Imperial Data Bank) - Yahoo!
It was also affected by the sluggish housing market and the progress of "consumer roofing away" due to repeated earthquake damage.
Kinki Ceramics Co., Ltd. (TDB Corporation Code: 530173983, capital of 92.2 million yen, 881-8 Otani, Awaji City, Hyogo Prefecture, representative Yukizo Fukuhara, and 44 employees) filed for quasi-self-insolvency at the Kobe District Court on August 30.
One applicant was Daichi Yoshida (Nishitenman 1-10-8, Kita Ward, Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture, and Daichi Yoshida Law Office, telephone 06-665-6038).
The company was founded in June 1895 and reorganized in April 1961.
At first, he started his business as a Ibushi tile maker in Nishitan-cho, Mihara County (now Minami-Awaji City) under the trade name of Kinki Kiln Co., Ltd.
In October 1986, Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd. merged into Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd. and succeeded the business of Kinki Sangyo Co., Ltd., but at the same time, the head office was relocated to its present location after changing its current business name.
After that, sales offices were established in Fukuyama City, Hiroshima City, Oita City, Miyazaki City, etc., and Juzen mainly used Ibushi tiles, but due to changes in consumer demand, Western-style tiles such as flat plate tiles were manufactured at a rate of 70 percent and Japanese-style tiles such as Ibushi tiles were 30%.
In the fiscal year ending December 2004, sales of approximately 3116 million yen were recorded.
He was known as the top tile maker of Awaji Island.
However, demand continued to grow due to the sluggish housing market following the Lehman shock and the frequent damage caused by the Great East Japan Earthquake and the Kumamoto Earthquake.
In terms of profits, in addition to the decline in the profit margin due to the surge in fuel prices, there was a continuous deficit with excessive interest-bearing debt associated with inventory burdens and business fixed investment, which forced severe financing.
For this reason, the Bank tried to rebuild its business by requesting financial institutions to ease the conditions for repayment of loans, but there was no sign of recovery in business conditions, and gradually the financial position was imminent.
I couldn't help but abandoned the business and this was the measure.
The debt is currently under investigation, but it is estimated to be about 2 billion yen.
The Prefectural Dinosaur Museum in Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture, which promotes "industrialization of tourism," is located in Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture.
Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture, announced on September 25 that it will acquire approximately 25,000 square meters of land adjacent to the construction site of the road station "Dinosaur Valley Katsuyama" which will open next spring.
In order to accelerate the "industrialization of tourism" advocated by the city and local economy, we aim to attract accommodation-specific hotels and restaurants.
A member of the board of directors explained the same day at the Special Committee on the Development of the City Council's Guest Base.
In addition to the opening of the Hokuriku Shinkansen in the spring of 2023, the entire section of the Chubu Ritsukan Expressway will be opened and the prefectural Dinosaur Museum (Katsuyama City) will be renovated and enhanced.
It is a private resting place next to the east of the road station building.
Surrounded by the Kuzuryu River, the Takinami River, and the prefectural road, it is twice as large as the road station (about 12,000 square meters).
In the name of the industrial complex, the City Land Development Corporation will proceed with land negotiations from this fiscal year, acquire land, and build land in FY21.
According to the city, there has already been a consultation from private businesses such as farmers' restaurants and harvesting facilities, fast food and restaurants.
As for accommodation, it was also revealed that Sekisui House has raised its name as a city to attract accommodation-specific hotels adjacent to roadside stations planned throughout Japan.
The Sekisui House is scheduled to expand into three locations in Fukui Prefecture, but it is said that several other cities will attract and compete.
The city also plans to build a parking lot.
The members asked for speed-up if the maintenance schedule was slow, and some members said that they would "do not have enough land to sleep."
Vice Mayor Sanekio Mizukami stated that he would like to appeal the superiority of Katsuyama City by taking the prefectural dinosaur museum and ski jam Katsuyama to the front as a tourism-themed industrial complex.
