BITPoint, which ran out of crypto assets worth 30 billion yen, will resume its service (Genyusha Gold Online) - Yahoo!
In July of this year, crypto asset exchanges, which amounted to 30 billion yen, such as Bitcoin, leaked illegally.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., the operating company, announced on September 30 that it would resume the sending (remittance) service of crypto assets.
There seems to be a certain point of view, including measures to prevent recurrence.
In July this year, BITPoint leaked Bitcoin and Ripple.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., which operates the Crypto Asset Exchange BITPoint, announced on September 27 that it plans to resume its Crypto Asset Transfer Service at around 14:00 on September 30.
In addition to dealing with customers who suffered damage and communicating with the Financial Services Agency, there seems to be a certain point of view, including measures to prevent recurrence, such as management system including security aspects.
Bitpoint Japan says, "We will resume our services as soon as possible and strive to recover the trust of our users while putting safety first."
In July of this year, the exchange encountered a cryptocurrency leak worth 30 billion yen, including Bitcoin and Ripple.
In the subsequent press conference, regarding the continuation of the business, he mentioned, "There is a current account balance of about 30 billion yen even if the compensation is deducted."
This article was released on September 27, 2019.
