1 year from the Eastern Iburi Earthquake: Water is secured even during power outage.
In response to the total power outage (blackout) caused by the Eastern Iburi Earthquake in September last year, measures are being taken at condominiums in Hakodate City, where dewatering occurred.
According to the city's Water and Wastewater Department, seven condominiums were installed in one year after the earthquake, and a "watering plug" was installed that could produce water even after a power outage.
There are about 400 condominiums and private housing units in the city that supply water with a "passenger tank" that could be cut off during a power outage.
The house's water supply system is broadly divided into two types: the "passenger tank" that once water is placed in the receiving water tank located underground or on the roof, and the "direct connection" that directly feeds each door from the city's water distribution pipe.
Even if the water pipe is not damaged, electric pumps that pump water from the water tank to each door will not be able to run due to power failure, and each door will be shut down.
Training (Aomori Broadcasting) - Yahoo!
A training session was held in Shingo Village to search and rescue people who had suffered before the autumn mushroom harvest season.
The training at Hirakozawa Forest Park in Shingo Village was attended by 60 people from police, fire and hunting parties.
At the opening ceremony, Mr. Fukuda, Chief of the Goto Police Department, called on him to work closely together and train.
★ takahashi Regional Manager's declaration "We will start mountain training and rescue training more than this."
The training was based on the assumption that a man who went out to see the mushroom harvest would not return home even at night.
The participants are divided into three groups and search through the mountains with the names of the missing men.
In Shingo Village, a 70-year-old man who entered the mountain in June was missing and was rescued the next day.
During the training, I found a man who was injured and checked the cooperation between search and rescue on the carrier and prepared for the autumn mushroom harvest season, which is prone to distress.
