The reason why YouTuber became a full-time employee.
I asked the president who hired me (bizSPA!).
9/27 (Fri) 8:47
YouTuber is now very popular with young people.
Although it is not uncommon for companies to use it to advertise their products, some companies have started a rare system called "YouTuber Adoption" that they employ as regular employees.
This is the direct marketing mix (DmMiX) of DmMiX, Inc., which is the main business of CRM (Customer Relationship Management).
What does it mean to adopt YouTuber?
Mr. Yuki Kobayashi, Representative Director of DmMiX and Representative Director of Staff First, a subsidiary adopted by YouTuber, talked about it.
i want to support young people who work hard with YouTuber.
What is YouTuber adoption in the first place?
Yuki Kobayashi: Now, YouTuber is a longing for many young people.
There are also top rankings in the career rankings that elementary school students want to get in the future.
Until now, we have adopted and supported young people who are chasing dreams such as bandmen and comedians.
In the same way, hiring young people who are chasing the dream of becoming YouTuber and trying to support them is YouTuber adoption.
There is an image that YouTuber is something that individuals voluntarily post videos, but why did you decide to adopt them?
Kobayashi: While many young people are longing for the profession of YouTuber, there is a reality that most YouTuber is not earning as much as they thought.
There are many creators who make and post videos while working part-time, and those who do not allow their family to recognize the existence of YouTuber.
In this initiative, we will provide an environment for salary and content creation to the creators we employ.
At first, we will support our activities by supporting the disadvantage of the profession of YouTuber, which will inevitably become unstable.
