Sakura Ebi in the Growth Process PT in Shizuoka City and 290 meters deep | Shizuoka Shimbun
Sakura Ebi (Sakura Ebi) was born this year in the deep sea of Suruga Bay.
The Yuhi Sakura Ebi Project, a project by an industry-academia-government organization such as Shizuoka City, succeeded in photographing sakura shrimp, which is believed to have been born during the spawning season this spring and summer, at a depth of 290 meters in Suruga Bay.
The video of the growth process is valuable, and the relevant parties want to lead to the elucidation of the ecology of sakura shrimp, which has many mysteries.
The photograph was taken near the bottom of the sea about 1 to 5 km off the coast of Gamora District, Shimizu Ward, City.
A total of 300 were confirmed in 17 minutes.
In the daytime, the traditional knowledge that sakura shrimp in the deep sea form a certain flock at the bottom of the sea was re-established.
The adult body is about 40 mm long, and the individual shown is about 23 mm long.
They identified the spawning season by matching data from season to season.
Detailed analysis is requested by Fujitsu Software Technologies and Shizuoka Institute of Technology, which make up the team.
Esuke Mizuno, Project Leader, said, "I want to capture the living figure of the individual in the growth process, including fry."
