New rates for mobile phones Price reduction in fair competition: Hokkaido Shimbun
A new fee plan for a mobile phone company was released as part of the revised Telecommunications Business Act of October.
However, it was generally stopped.
Chief Cabinet Secretary Yoshihide SUGAWARA said last summer, "There is room to lower the price by about 40%," and despite the high expectations for price reduction, price competition did not occur.
It is a major factor that Rakuten's full-scale entry was postponed, and the oligod status of three major companies continued.
It is desirable for consumers to become an easy-to-use pricing system by fair competition.
I want to ask for their efforts.
The amendment prohibits a set discount on terminal and communication charges.
Instead of selling the terminal fee, the communication fee was set to increase.
Softbank and KDDI (au) announced plans to make the terminal a maximum of half.
However, both companies have a SIM lock that cannot be used by other companies for 100 days.
NTT Docomo makes up to one-third of the terminals for subscribers of its own lines.
The three companies continue to "enclosure" to prevent transfers to other companies.
The Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications announced that it would require immediate termination of SIM locking.
Companies must respond quickly.
The delay in Rakuten was due to the lack of infrastructure such as base stations.
It was expected to be an explosive in price reduction competition, so it was dressed in a shoulder strap.
It was probably the sweetness of the outlook.
The timing and prices of full-scale services have not been disclosed.
As a company responsible for social infrastructure, we would like to take responsibility for our business.
This revision of the price was triggered by the remarks of Chief Cabinet Secretary Suga.
Mr. Suga complained about the new charges of the three companies: "I think competition will start in the future, and I don't think it's going to be okay."
However, the government-made price reduction will distort the market and encourage sound competition.
The company should develop customer-oriented competition before it is announced by the government.
The cost system of each company is very complex and it is not easy to compare.
The Consumer Affairs Agency called attention to the fact that there are cases where the consumer's burden exceeds half the amount while the terminal advertises such as "maximum half."
Companies must make careful and easy-to-understand explanations to avoid misunderstandings.
Cash card of 3 Shinkin in Mie Prefecture - Ise Shimbun
Three Shinkin Banks in Mie Prefecture (Kuwana Mie Shinkin Bank, Kita Ise Ueno Shinkin Bank, and Kihoku Shinkin Bank) announced on July 26 that they decided to reduce the amount of withdrawal by cash card to prevent damage to special scams.
In the past three years, the maximum amount for depositors aged 70 or older who have not made a certain amount of withdrawal transactions at ATMs (automated cash depositors) is 500,000 yen, which can be made daily by cash card.
On October 1, the Kuwana Mie Shinkin Bank and the Kita-Ise Ueno Shinkin Bank lowered the Kihoku Shinkin Bank from November 1.
In the prefecture, there are many special fraud cases in which cash cards and PINs are stolen by financial institutions and police officials, etc., and those involved in the Shinkin Bank "want to protect customers' important deposits in the best possible way."
