PokeTalk is a portable translation machine that provides free loan to 500 stores in Hamamatsu City.
The Hamamatsu Chamber of Commerce and Industry announced on July 26 that it had completed the installation of 500 portable translation machines at its member offices, including stores in Hamamatsu.
It is said that it is the first time in Japan to deploy the translator in a concentrated manner in the same area, and it is attracting attention whether it will improve the ability to respond to inbound tourists.
The loans included 236 restaurants, 113 retail stores, 17 accommodations, and 134 others.
The city has 60% of its population.
The map app "Google Map" started to show where to rent, and the location of "stores for foreign languages" can be seen on smartphones.
It is accessible from the site of Lake Hamana Tourism Area.
The free loan of Poketók, which corresponds to 74 languages, was initiated in April in response to the declaration of Hamamatsu, the largest inbound support city in Japan by nine organizations in the city.
The Chamber purchases 500 units and lends them to small and medium-sized businesses that meet the requirements of obtaining hospitality certification and introducing cashless payments for two years.
The representative of the Chamber of Commerce said, "We want foreign customers to develop new customers while the business environment is severe."
