Yamagata City | Yamagata Shimbun
A bidder for the children's play facility and the Minaminumahara Elementary School was decided by Yamagata City, which is planning to build a social capital (PFI) system using private funds, and an explanation of the facility was given at the Standing Committee of the City Council held on the 26th.
Image of a children's play facility established in Kataya, Yamagata City
The children's play facility is scheduled to be built on the north side of Yamagata Kuchu in Kataya District, with an area of approximately 234 square meters.
The building has a total floor area of about 3,000 square meters.
It has a semi-underground gymnasium, cafe and book corner.
It also features a universal design playground that allows children with disabilities to play outdoors, ensuring 300 parking spaces.
On the 5th of this month, a committee meeting was held at the city hall, and 13 shelter groups (Yamagata City) won the bid for 355 million yen including design, preparation for opening, maintenance and operation expenses for 15 years.
Design and construction will begin in January next year and will be open in March 2022.
Image of Minaminumabara Elementary School
The school has over 900 children.
It is planned to be built on the north side of the current school building in Iizawa City, with an area of about 25,000 square meters.
It is a three-story reinforced concrete building with a total floor area of 8580 square meters.
There are 30 classrooms, two pools, a steel gymnasium, and a children's club.
At the committee meeting on 6th of this month, the Ichimura Corporation Group (Yamagata City), consisting of eight companies, won the bid for 4.512.1 million yen including design, demolition of old school buildings, and maintenance and operation expenses for 15 years.
It was designed and built in December and will be completed in October 22.
