Publication of the original manuscript before the suicide of Akutagawa | Shizuoka Shimbun
A manuscript written by Ryunosuke Akutagawa, who was first published in the Tabata Bunshi Village Memorial Hall.
The author Ryunosuke AKUTAGAWA (1892-1927) published his essay "Shoku Bungeshi-mura Memorial Hall in Kita-ku, Tokyo" by himself in his last years of fighting literature with Junichiro Tanizaki.
It will be exhibited at the museum from October 1.
Although it was known that his essay was included in the whole collection, it was the first time that his manuscript was published publicly.
It is said that he wrote a few months before Akutagawa committed suicide, and the museum researcher Jo Isai said, "I can see that Akutagawa, who had fallen physically and mentally, faced serious literary challenges with a tragic determination."
A total of 12 essays containing 200 characters were published in the April 27 issue of "Bornography Spring Autumn."
