Jaguar F-PACE, the first big improvement ...The possibility of hybridization (response) - Yahoo!News
Jaguar's first crossover SUV, "F-PACE" The camera captured the new prototype for the first time in Southern Europe.
F-PACE originated from the 4-seater concept SUV C-X17, which was first released in 2013.
The five-seat version was released in 2014 and officially debuted at the Frankfurt Motor Show in 2015.
The next year, the original model was released, and this is the first facelift.
The prototype captured is covered with thick camouflage, but part of the new design can be seen.
The headlights are more compact and thin, and the side air intake seems to have been fixed to a sporty oval.
The grill is completely disguised, but it will definitely be redesigned.
In the rear end, a portion of the redesigned taillight, which is equipped with a narrow reverse light at the top, can be seen.
As in the current model, there is a possibility that the design that moves greatly to the side is compactly modified.
The cabin is expected to be equipped with the company's touch screen infotainment system and will refresh new digital clusters, HVAC control screens, steering wheels, and gear selectors.
The powertrain is expected to include a 2.0-litre four-cylinder turbodiesel and a hybrid 3.0-litre six-cylinder indium.
The world premiere will be in 2020.
