"I'll kill you" (KTS Kagoshima TV) - Yahoo!News
On the 24th of this month, a 33-year-old unemployed man was arrested on a national highway in Kagoshima City for allegedly threatening to "kill" the man who was driving.
The suspect who was arrested on suspicion of intimidation was Katsu Miyahara (33) who was unemployed in Karaminato 4-chome, Kagoshima City.
According to the police, suspect Miyahara was suspected of threatening a man at a crossing over Kagoshima City on the national highway at 0:00 a.m. this month.
On the 25th, the man submitted the damage report and the police proceeded to investigate, but on the afternoon of the 26th, a suspect Miyahara went to the police station with a friend saying, "I was afraid the video of driving was taken up on TV and SNS."
Mr. Miyahara admits the charges and says about his motive, "I was forced to brake."
The police investigate the suspect Miyahara was driving without a license.
