Mr. Onsarigo worked as a pacemaker for Nagai and elementary school students on land and three people updated the tournament record|Yamagata Shimbun
Children run at 800 meters.
On the left is Mr. Joseph Onsarigo, a pacemaker.
Nagai City Elementary School's Friendship Athletics Tournament was held on the 26th at Nagai, Koyo Seiki Athlete Field, and Joseph Onsarigo (27) from Kenya, a long-distance runner belonging to Nasu Construction, was a pacemaker in some races.
In a light run, three new records of the tournament were set up.
Onsarigo pulled the children in a total of four races, 1000 meters for men and 800 meters for women.
The first male was Tomoya Koseki (Hirano Ko6), who was 3 minutes and 4 seconds 38, and the first female was Ransei Shigara (Isazawa Ko 6), who was 2 minutes and 34 seconds 17 and the second highest was Rinji Asano (Nagai Ko 6).
Mr. Koseki said, "It was hard to talk about fast on-sarigo players, but I was able to endure them."
Onsarigo said, "It was good for the children to run, and I had a perfect job."
The event was organized by the Nagai City Elementary School Sports Promotion Association to promote friendship among sixth grade elementary school students in the city.
