Leading-edge art in the world Okayama Art Exchange opens in the center of the city: Sanyo Shimbun Digital | San Diego
People around the classroom who will be the stage for a video work depicting the future 3,000 years later
The International Art Exhibition "Okayama Art Exchange 2019" held every three years in the center of Okayama City (hosted by the Executive Committee created in cities and prefectures) opened on the 27th.
Along with the mysterious title "IF THE SNAKE If Snake," 18 artists from 9 countries enjoy cutting-edge art created by art fans both in Japan and abroad.
This is the second time following 16 years, with French artist Pierre Yuigu as artistic director, he develops works that utilize Okayama's climate and local resources.
Approximately 40 films and three-dimensional works will be shown at 13 locations including the former Uchiyama Shimoko (Marunouchi, Kita Ward, Okayama City) and the prefectural Tenjinyama Cultural Plaza.
Prior to the opening, a small opening ceremony was held, and about 100 people attended.
Mr. Masao Omori, Mayor of the Executive Committee, and Mr. Yasuharu Ishikawa, General Producer of the Executive Committee, gave a speech and cut the tape, saying, "The works that stimulate intellectual sensibility, and the imagination and creativity have come together, and become an exhibition that attracts attention from the world."
The families and children who visited the school immediately saw a snake-shaped robot that reacts to the sound of the surrounding area in the dohyo in the school yard, and walked around the school building that changed into the stage of a video work depicting the world 3,000 years later.
I enjoyed the art that came to a different world.
When I was traveling with my father, a first-year high school student in Tokyo (15) said, "It's interesting to imagine the atmosphere of the old school building.
It is closed on November 24 (the following day for national holidays).
Hong Kong rally in five years of rain umbrella movement tens of thousands, aiming for ordinary elections | Shizuoka Shimbun
Five years have passed since the "Amembrance Movement" started, and people gathered at the meeting venue = 28th Hong Kong (co-operation)
[Collaboration with Hong Kong] On the 28th of May, a large-scale demonstration in 2014 called the "Ambrella Movement," which sought to democratize the election of the Chief Executive of Hong Kong, a rally of tens of thousands was held in a park near the Hong Kong Government Office Building in Admiralty, where the largest demonstration unit was located.
Some young people took over the main road around the venue and threw fire bottles into the government building.
As protest activities started with the amendment of the Fugitive Act continued, the participants renewed their determination to fight until the realization of a "true ordinary election" that could not be won at the time.
The full-scale protests in June took over 112 days, exceeding 79 days of the rain umbrella movement, and the demands of the demonstrators expanded to "five major demands" such as electoral reform.
Ibaraki Kokutai Opens today 28th | Saga News|Saga Shimbun
The 74th National Sports Festival "Ikii Ibaraki Yume Kokutai 2019" was held on 28th, and the general opening ceremony was held at Kasamatsu Sports Park Athletic Stadium in Hidanaka City, Ibaraki Prefecture.
The Saga Prefectural Team will compete in 33 competitions, including athletes and directors, and will challenge the nation's strong athletes with pride in their hometown.
The prefecture ranks 43rd for three consecutive years until last year, but rose to 33rd last year.
The goal of this year is to reach the first half of the 20th place.
In the pre-season competition held by the 16th, the Saga Women's High School of Gymnastics Boys and Girls of Gymnastics and the Jonen Women and Girls of Gymnastics won 6th place and played.
In each competition, we aim to advance to the top.
At the opening ceremony, 83 athletes, directors, and officers of the headquarters marched on the 40th floor of the prefectural government, and a rugby boy, Kugo Ishikawa (Saga Koko), became the flagbearer.
On the first day, wrestling, table tennis and karate are held.
